{
  "stem": "23645.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Unbeknownst to me, 50 years later, there's a book that came out in French, the one that I showed you, where some of the prisoners, some German, some Russians, and some other nationalities that were in there that were sort of the leadership of the camp, they were political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "One of them, for instance, we called him Willie, was a 5-foot little German, who, in 1938 said, Mr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Hitler, I don't agree with Nazism.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So they threw him into camp rather than killing him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And he was instrumental in one-- at one occasion when-- when we were marched out before April 1945, a few days earlier.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They were trying to get all the Jews out there to kill them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we were standing on-- on-- on a-- on a pell to be counted.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And this Gestapo man, with his stick, you know, banging, and his shoes, walked over and he says, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "All Jews step forward.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And Willie, he sort of glanced at both Chopnik and myself and winked at us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he says to him, Ich haben nicht keine Juden.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I don't have any Jews here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And he knew we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So Willie that day saved our lives, because those that were marched out, most of them didn't survive.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because some of these kids-- some of these elders, you know-- unbeknownst to me, this book came out-- and they took it upon themselves to do everything possible to shelter these children.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Over-- some close to 3,000 children went through Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for all these years, they thought that they failed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it-- and it wasn't known.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they didn't brag about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they managed to save a thousand.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Suddenly I said to myself, why are things so good for us in here, to Chopnik and I?",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
